1 Section 325.20. A. In lieu of an automatic fire extinguishing
2 system, portable fire extinguishers shall be installed in mobile
3 food establishments that produce All mobile food preparation
4 vehicles operating within this state prior to July 1, 2024, that are
5 capable of producing smoke or grease-laden vapors shall be in
6 compliance with the most current adopted fire code. With the
7 exception of an automatic fire extinguishing system, such
8 requirement shall apply to vehicles including, but not limited to,
9 vehicles utilizing electric energy, liquefied petroleum gas,
10 compressed natural gas, or a combination thereof for cooking,
11 provided that portable fire extinguishers are installed and
12 maintained in accordance with the most current version of NFPA 10:
13 Standard for Portable Fire Extinguishers. All fire extinguishers
14 shall be inspected annually by a licensed contractor. A six-liter
15 Class K-rated, portable fire extinguisher is required for all
16 cooking equipment involving solid fuels or vegetable or animal oils
17 and fats or a combination thereof. All portable fire extinguishers
18 shall be in clear view and immediately available for use.
19 B. The provisions of this section shall cease to have the force
20 and effect of law on November 1, 2025 All liquefied petroleum gas
