3 D. Mobile food preparation vehicles shall be under the sole
4 jurisdiction of the State Fire Marshal and shall be inspected
5 annually by the State Fire Marshal to ensure compliance with the
6 latest version of the state-adopted minimum codes for fire and life
7 safety as adopted by the Oklahoma Uniform Building Code Commission.
8 The State Fire Marshall shall coordinate, at minimum, annual
9 inspections conducted:
10 1. Within each of the four quadrants of this state; and
11 2. Twice within each county with a population exceeding four
12 hundred thousand (400,000) according to the latest Federal Decennial
13 Census.
14 E. Upon approval, the State Fire Marshal shall issue an
15 operational permit decal indicating that the vehicle meets the
16 minimum fire code requirements as currently adopted at the time of
17 inspection.
18 F. Nothing in this act shall prevent the State Fire Marshal
19 from enforcing the minimum fire code requirements as allowed by law
20 and revoking the operations of a mobile food preparation vehicle for
21 cause when it is determined to be inherently dangerous to the
22 health, safety, or welfare of persons within this state.
23 G. Nothing in this act shall prevent a political subdivision
24 from enforcing the event permits, operational fees, land use
Req. No. 2070 Page 3

1 regu lations, zoning, and other ordinances in relation to the
2 operation of a mobile food preparation vehicle within the boundaries
3 of the political subdivision.
4 H. The State Fire Marshal may promulgate rules necessary to
5 implement the provisions of this section. Such rules shall have
6 uniform force and effect throughout this state and no political
7 subdivision or other agency shall enact or enforce any fire or life
8 safety code-related ordinances, rules, or other requirements for
9 mobile food preparation vehicles, except in a county with a
10 population exceeding four hundred thousand (400,000) according to
11 the latest Federal Decennial Census.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
